          Clostridium acetobutylicum and its 
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">S.</ENAMEX> paratyphi A ortholog
          correspondingly retrieved 
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">S.</ENAMEX> cerevisiae <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">RAD52</ENAMEX> and its
          eukaryotic homologs, with borderline e-values at
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">convergence</ENAMEX> (<NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">~0.043</NUMEX>). The alignment between these
          <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">bacterial proteins</ENAMEX> and the eukaryotic <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">Rad52</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT_DESC">homologs</ENAMEX> was
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">co</ENAMEX>-linear throughout the entire length of their shared
