          (hereinafter the <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">RAD52</NUMEX> superfamily).
          The secondary structure predictions showed that the
          Rad52 <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">superfamily proteins</ENAMEX> adopt a <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">structure</ENAMEX> with
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">interspersed α</ENAMEX>-helices and <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">β-strands</NUMEX> (<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Fig</ENAMEX>. <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">5</NUMEX>).
          Additionally, fold predictions using 3DPSSM
          (<ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">E-</ENAMEX>value=<NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">.0085</NUMEX>, corresponding to a <NUMEX TYPE="PERCENT">90%</NUMEX> confidence in the
          prediction) and the hybrid fold method (<ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Z</ENAMEX>-score = <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">19.5</NUMEX>)
          predicted the presence of a potential <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE">Helix-hairpin-Helix</ENAMEX>
          (<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">HhH</ENAMEX>) fold in <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">members</ENAMEX> of the <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">RAD52</NUMEX> superfamily. The HhH
