          superfamilies, at least the bacterial RAD52-proteins
          might be of predominantly phage origin. The core of the
          eukaryotic recombination system appears to have been
          inherited from the system present in the common ancestor
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">shared</ENAMEX> with the archaea [ <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">29</TIMEX> ] . However, <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">RAD52</ENAMEX> is thus
