          case, it appears that the pre-existing ERF gene was
          displaced through the insertion of a bacterial RAD52-like
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">gene</ENAMEX>. Interestingly, and in the same vein, the RecT
          <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">proteins</ENAMEX> from 
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ANIMAL">Bacillus species</ENAMEX> contain a short
          C-terminal acidic module that is missing in other RecT
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">proteins</ENAMEX>, but is highly similar to the <ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">C-</ENAMEX>terminal region
